{
  "stem": "26728.7",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I took them out to my crew chief and I said, Louis, can we-- we used carbon tetrachloride a lot.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For-- you know what that is?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's a real strong chemical that-- that, uh, evaporates almost instantly, but it's very deadly, which we didn't know at the time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, if you absorbed it in your skin, it gets in your liver and it stays there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Whatever carbon tetrachloride I have ever handled in my whole life is still in my liver.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It stays there, and if you get too much it kills you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyhow, I said, Louis, I want to-- well, we used to use it for cleaning our uniforms and cleaning tools and stuff, too.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It cut grease like nobody's business, and it had a medicinal type odor to it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I said, I want to clean my, uh, my flight suit, my pinks, and my, uh, underwear and my-- and my B-8 jacket with carbon tet.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had it in these big cans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he said, OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We got a big can and-- and put all the stuff in there and we sloshed it around.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And carbon tet does not burn.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It is also is a flame retardant, and some extinguishers have carbon tetrachloride in them and it puts out-- it smothers a fire.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A small fire.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's not any good anymore because they have better stuff.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So anyhow, we sloshed this stuff around and I hung it on the fence, and I told Louis about the smell.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I said, do you smell that, Louis?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That smells like shit?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Smells like dead dogs, dead--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said, no, it smells kind of bad, but I don't smell that smell.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
